Queen and senior members of the Royal Family will attend Westminster Abbey service of thanksgiving on May 8 to mark 70th anniversary of Victory in Europe (VE) Day . 
  Chain of beacons will be lit across the country and a star-studded concert will be held in London . 
  On May 8, 1945 the Queen joined the jubilant victory celebrations . 
  The Queen will lead the nation at a religious service . 
 